f=Governance/precedent/custom/ruling-log/SKILL.md · in=ruling-log precedent's capture skill: board ruling constitutional rulings, vetoes their appeals, fiduciary recommendations operator overrules, risk rulings gets recorded one standard schema, tagged article/commitment topic, future gate requests answered "here's what ruled before, why." write-side institutional memory; `consistency-check` `case-law-method` read-side. · p=Board's rulings valuable their retrievability. unlogged ruling gets re-litigated; untagged one can't found; one recorded without rationale can't applied next case. skill makes ruling durable, findable, reasoned record difference between governance function series one-off opinions. · wu=Triggers: "log ruling," "record decision," "past rulings [topic]," automatically whenever board completes gate review (board's skills already log; skill owns schema retrieval). · st:/ Protocol=`Capture the ruling in the standard schema (assets/ruling-schema.md) \· -> Tag: article/commitment cited + topic(s) + venture/scope \· -> Append to the configured decision log (never overwrite) \· -> On any new gate request: surface the top 3 most similar precedents` · h3:Phase 1 — Capture=Record `assets/ruling-schema.md`: ruling ID, date, decision under review (one line), gate(s) ran, ruling gate, **rationale** (the "because" valuable field, blueprint's decisions-with-reasoning rule), articles/commitments/thresholds cited verbatim, operator's final call differed, outcome known later. Never backfill rationale memory reasoning wasn't stated ruling time, record "rationale captured" rather reconstructing it. · h3:Phase 2 — Tag=Tag record with: article/commitment IDs cited (from business's constitution/commitments), 1–3 topic tags (spend, hiring, partnership, venture-launch, etc. grown business, fixed taxonomy), scope (which venture/unit). Tags retrieval; keep them consistent check existing tags before minting new ones. · h3:Phase 3 — Append=Append configured decision log (`decision_log_destination`, shared board's config). Append-only: corrections new entries referencing old ID, never edits consistent sentinel's audit-trail-method immutability principle. · h3:Phase Surface Precedents=new gate request arrives (board routes before ruling), search log article/commitment topic tags return **top similar prior rulings**, as: ruling ID, one-line case, ruling rationale, it's similar. fewer exist, return what exists; none, say "no precedent point" never stretch unrelated ruling relevance. What board *does* precedents `case-law-method`'s `consistency-check`'s territory. · of=`## Precedents for: [new case, one line] \·  \· \| # \| Ruling ID / date \| Case \| Ruling \| Why similar \| \· \|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| \· [top 3, or fewer, or "no precedent on point"]` · of=capture: completed schema record (see assets). retrieval: · pr=**Rationale record.** ruling without "because" half-logged., **Append-only, corrections reference.** immutability discipline sentinel's audit trail., **Tags grown, invented upfront.** Reuse before minting; taxonomy nobody follows worse none., **No precedent means precedent.** Don't stretch weak matches; say so., **Log overrule too.** operator overrules board, that's often instructive record log. · f=Decision log destination unset deliver records operator directly, flag config gap., ruling arrives without stated rationale record "rationale captured," flag board., Log grows large scan propose index (one line ruling blueprint's INDEX.md pattern) maintenance task; don't silently truncate retrieval. · b:with Other precedent Skills=ruling-log **records retrieves**; `case-law-method` governs retrieved precedent *applied distinguished*; `consistency-check` runs contradiction test between *proposed* ruling retrieved set., Boundary board: board's skills produce rulings already log them; skill owns schema, tags, retrieval. Board consumes top-3 precedents start gate review.